 
 
 
 
Advance Excel Assignment 1 
 
1.	What do you mean by cells in an excel sheet? 

Ans :- Cells is the unit of excel sheet , Each cell is identified by a unique reference , typically denoted by a combination of its column letter and row number . Cells can contain various type of data like string , number , date .

2.	How can you restrict someone from copying a cell from your worksheet? 
Ans :- Via using the lock sheet option restrict someone from copying a cell , like follow this way …
select the cell to protect
open the format cell 
navigate the protection tab 
uncheck the lock option and make a password and permission.
 
3.	How to move or copy the worksheet into another workbook? 
Ans :- Select the sheet and press Ctrl+C(For copy) / Ctrl+Z (For move)and go there you wants to copy and press Ctrl+V(for paste).
 
4.	Which key is used as a shortcut for opening a new window document? 
Ans :- Ctrl + N 
 
5.	What are the things that we can notice after opening the Excel interface? 
Ans:- First we open Excel there are many tab and menu ,
Ribbon : Home , insert , page , and so on 
Worksheet area : there are cells that make complete worksheet .
Row and column
Cell cursor 
formula bar 
and many such things …

 
6.	When to use a relative cell reference in excel? 
Ans : - Relative cell reference , when we wants to copying formula , Repeating a calculation pattern , Creating Dynamic Referance..



 
 
 
 
 
